            "raw_output": {
              "output": "<task id=\"ses_15779e984ffefJOXb6ZARbNvwN\" state=\"completed\">\n<task_result>\nNow I have a thorough picture. Here is the comprehensive summary:\n\n---\n\n# Comprehensive Project Analysis: Russian ASR ITN Hybrid\n\n## 1. Top-Level Directory Structure\n\n```\n/home/redalexdad/GitHub/Russian-ASR-ITN-Hybrid/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 .agents/           # Agent configuration (commit-review skill)\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 .dockerignore\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 .git/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 .githooks/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 .gitignore\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 .ipynb_checkpoints/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 .pytest_cache/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 .venv/             # Python virtual environment\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 .zed/              # Zed editor settings\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 answer.f           # Output file (predicted normalizations)\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 data/              # Datasets (.feather format)\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 docker-compose.yml # Docker Compose v2 configuration\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Dockerfile          # Multi-stage Docker build\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 docs/              # Project documentation (9 markdown files)\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 LICENSE            # MIT License\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 main.ipynb         # Jupyter notebook entry\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 main.py            # Main Python entry point\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Makefile            # Root Makefile (includes modules)\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 makefiles/         # Makefile modules (6 .mk files)\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Migrate.chat\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 mlflow-artifacts/  # MLflow experiment artifacts\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 mlflow.db          # MLflow tracking database\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 models/            # Trained models (ruT5-itn/, char_ngram.pkl)\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 pytest.ini         # Pytest configuration\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 README.md          # Project readme\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 reports/           # Experiment reports and plans (37 files)\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 requirements.txt   # Python dependencies\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 scripts/           # Utility scripts (6 files)\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 src/               # Core source code\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 task/              # Original assignment description\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 tests/             # Unit tests\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 untitled.chat / untitled1.chat / untitled2.chat / untitled3.chat\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 \u0440\u0430\u0437\u043d\u044b\u0435/            # Miscellaneous\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. Full `src/` Directory Tree\n\n```\nsrc/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 __init__.py                       # Empty (package marker)\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 __pycache__/                      # Python bytecode cache\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 cli.py                            # CLI entry points (run/evaluate/errors)\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 disambiguate.py                   # POS disambiguation (pymorphy2 + heuristics)\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 eda.py                            # Lightweight EDA statistics for CLI\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 hybrid.py                         # Hybrid: rule-based parser + ruT5 fallback\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 lexicon.py                        # Dictionary assembly and lookup functions\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 ngram_lm.py                       # Character-level n-gram language model\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 normalizer.py                     # Main text normalization pipeline\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 parser.py                         # Number group parser (sum vs enumeration)\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 sequence_parser.py                # New state-machine sequence parser\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 token_classifier.py               # Token classification (root-based + dictionary)\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 dicts/\n    \u251c\u2500\u2500 __init__.py                   # Empty (package marker)\n    \u251c\u2500\u2500 __pycache__/\n    \u251c\u2500\u2500 asr_errors.py                 # ASR error corrections (~40 mappings)\n    \u251c\u2500\u2500 hundreds.py                   # Hundreds dictionary (100-900)\n    \u251c\u2500\u2500 ordinals.py                   # Ordinal numerals dictionary (1st-900th)\n    \u251c\u2500\u2500 thousands.py                  # Multipliers: thousands, millions, billions\n    \u2514\u2500\u2500 units.py                      # Units (0-9), teens (10-19), tens (20-90)\n```\n\nSupporting directories:\n\n```\nscripts/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 eda.py                    # Extended EDA with 8 plots/graphs\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 fetch_real_data.py        # Real data collection from Wikipedia + RSS\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 generate_synthetic.py     # Synthetic dataset generation (700 lines)\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 train.py                  # ruT5-small fine-tuning with LoRA + MLflow\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 train_ngram_lm.py         # Character n-gram LM training\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 validate_notebook.py      # Jupyter notebook validation\n\ntests/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 test_parser.py            # Tests for parser.parse_number_group (9 tests)\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 test_sequence_parser.py   # Tests for token_classifier + sequence_parser (18 tests)\n\ndata/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 calibration.f             # 500 labeled rows (ground truth provided)\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 raw_sentences.json        # Raw scraped sentences\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 real.f                    # 165 real-world rows (from Wikipedia/RSS)\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 synthetic.f               # ~16,500 synthetic rows (generated)\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 test.f                    # 500 unlabeled rows (target for answer.f)\n\nmodels/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 char_ngram.pkl            # Trained char n-gram LM\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 ruT5-itn/                 # Fine-tuned ruT5-small + LoRA adapters\n\ndocs/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 architecture.md           # Overall architecture and module description\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 cli.md                    # CLI and Makefile usage guide\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 data.md                   # Dataset descriptions\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 full_report.md            # Full project report\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 hybrid.md                 # Hybrid parser + ruT5 approach\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 lexicon.md                # Dictionary and ASR error documentation\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 normalizer.md             # Normalizer internals\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 parser.md                 # Parser logic details\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 training.md               # Training ruT5-small with LoRA\n\nmakefiles/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 commands.mk               # Docker container commands\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 config.mk                 # Configuration variables\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 docker.mk                 # Docker lifecycle (build/up/down/deploy/clean)\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 help.mk                   # Help/usage\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 local.mk                  # Local (without Docker) commands\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 mlflow.mk                 # MLflow management\n\nreports/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 2026-06-05_*.md           # Timestamped experiment reports\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 2026-06-06_*.md           # More experiment reports\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 2026-06-07_*.md           # More experiment reports\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 plan_lora_and_overfitting.md\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 plan_mlflow_integration.md\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 plan_sequence_parser.md\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 plan_synthetic_real_data.md\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 plan_to_99_percent.md\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 template.md\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 training_analysis_ep20_57pct.md\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 plots/                    # EDA-generated plots\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. What the Project Does\n\n**Russian ASR ITN Hybrid** solves **Inverse Text Normalization (ITN)** for numerical expressions in Russian ASR (Automatic Speech Recognition) transcriptions.\n\n### Core Problem\nPhone conversations between managers and clients contain many numerical values (prices, budgets, dates, quantities). ASR systems produce these numbers in written form -- often with recognition errors, missing letters, fused words, and other distortions. For example:\n\n> `\"\u0431\u044e\u0434\u0436\u0435\u0442 \u0433\u0434\u0435 \u0442\u043e \u0442\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0430 \u043f\u0435\u0442\u044c\u0434\u0435\u0441\u044f\u0442 \u0442\u044b\u0441\u0438\u0447 \u0440\u0443\u0431\u043b\u0435\u0438\"`\n\nThis project converts such written-out numbers back into their digital form:\n\n> `\"\u0431\u044e\u0434\u0436\u0435\u0442 \u0433\u0434\u0435 \u0442\u043e 350000 \u0440\u0443\u0431\u043b\u0435\u0439\"`\n\n### Key Capabilities\n- **Rule-based parser**: Uses a large dictionary of Russian numeral forms (including grammatical case inflections), ASR error correction mappings, and magnitude-based grouping logic to distinguish between **summation** (200 + 50 = 250) and **enumeration** (200, 300 = two separate numbers).\n- **ASR error robustness**: Maintains a curated dictionary of ~40 common ASR distortions (e.g., \"\u0434\u0432\u0435\u0441\u0438\" -> \"\u0434\u0432\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0438\", \"\u0442\u044b\u0449\" -> \"\u0442\u044b\u0441\u044f\u0447\", \"\u043f\u0435\u0442\u044c\u0441\u044f\u0442\" -> \"\u043f\u044f\u0442\u044c\u0434\u0435\u0441\u044f\u0442\").\n- **Hybrid fallback**: Optionally uses a fine-tuned **ruT5-small** transformer model (65M parameters, with LoRA adapters) to handle low-confidence cases.\n- **Sequence-based parser (new)**: A state-machine alternative pipeline using `token_classifier.py` + `sequence_parser.py`.\n\n### Performance\n| Dataset | Accuracy | Errors |\n|---|---|---|\n| calibration.f | **97.6%** | 12/500 |\n| synthetic.f (clean) | 96.32% | -- |\n| real.f | 83.0% | 17% |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Key Technologies, Languages, and Frameworks\n\n**Main Language:**\n- **Python 3.12** -- all source code, scripts, tests, and infrastructure\n\n**Core Technologies:**\n\n| Technology | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| **Polars** | Data processing (reading/writing `.feather` files, data manipulation) |\n| **PyTorch** (>=2.0) | Deep learning framework for ruT5 model |\n| **Transformers** (HuggingFace, >=4.30) | Seq2Seq model loading and training |\n| **PEFT** (>=0.10) | LoRA parameter-efficient fine-tuning |\n| **MLflow** (>=2.0) | Experiment tracking, metric logging, model versioning |\n| **Docker + Compose v2** | Containerization with multi-stage build |\n| **Matplotlib + Seaborn** | EDA visualization (8+ plot types) |\n| **pytest** | Unit testing (27 tests across 2 test files) |\n| **pymorphy2** | POS disambiguation for ambiguous words (e.g., \"\u0441\u0442\u043e\" as numeral vs verb) |\n| **BeautifulSoup4 + requests** | Web scraping for real data collection |\n| **sentencepiece / protobuf** | Tokenizer dependencies for ruT5 |\n| **scikit-learn** | Classification reports during model evaluation |\n| **gdown** | Google Drive file download |\n\n**Infrastructure:**\n- **Make** -- Build system with modular `.mk` files\n- **Git** -- Version control with custom `.githooks/`\n- **Jupyter** -- `main.ipynb` notebook for interactive exploration\n\n---\n\n## 5. Main Entry Points and Project Organization\n\n### Entry Points\n\n1. **`main.py`** (root) -- The primary CLI entry point. Delegates to `src.cli.main()`:\n   ```bash\n   python main.py run data/test.f -o answer.f      # Normalize and save\n   python main.py evaluate data/calibration.f       # Evaluate accuracy\n   python main.py errors data/calibration.f -n 15   # Show errors\n   ```\n\n2. **`Makefile`** (root) -- Orchestrates all operations via modular includes:\n   ```bash\n   make deploy            # Docker: down + build + up\n   make run               # Normalization inside container\n   make evaluate          # Accuracy evaluation inside container\n   make train             # Train ruT5 via Docker\n   make train-local       # Train locally via .venv\n   make eda               # Full EDA with plots\n   ```\n\n### Project Organization Architecture\n\n```\n                        \u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510\n                        \u2502   main.py   \u2502\n                        \u2502 (Entrypoint)\u2502\n                        \u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u252c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518\n                               \u2502\n                        \u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u25bc\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510\n                        \u2502  src/cli.py \u2502\n                        \u2502 run/eval/err\u2502\n                        \u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u252c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518\n                               \u2502\n          \u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u253c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510\n          \u2502                    \u2502                     \u2502\n   \u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u25bc\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510    \u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u25bc\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510    \u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u25bc\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510\n   \u2502normalizer.py\u2502    \u2502  hybrid.py    \u2502    \u2502     eda.py      \u2502\n   \u2502(Text walk)  \u2502    \u2502(Parser+ruT5)  \u2502    \u2502(Lightweight EDA)\u2502\n   \u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u252c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518    \u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518    \u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518\n          \u2502\n   \u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u25bc\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510\n   \u2502  parser.py  \u2502  \u2190\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500 sequence_parser.py (alternative)\n   \u2502 (Sum/Enum)  \u2502\n   \u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u252c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518\n          \u2502\n   \u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u25bc\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510\n   \u2502  lexicon.py \u2502  \u2190\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500 token_classifier.py (classify tokens)\n   \u2502 (Lookup)    \u2502\n   \u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u252c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518\n          \u2502\n   \u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2534\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510\n   \u2502         dicts/              \u2502\n   \u2502 \u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u252c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u252c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u252c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510 \u2502\n   \u2502 \u2502units\u2502hundred\u2502thous \u2502ord  \u2502 \u2502\n   \u2502 \u2502.py  \u2502s.py  \u2502ands  \u2502inals\u2502 \u2502\n   \u2502 \u2502     \u2502      \u2502.py   \u2502.py  \u2502 \u2502\n   \u2502 \u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2534\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2534\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2534\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518 \u2502\n   \u2502         asr_errors.py       \u2502\n   \u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518\n```\n\n### Data Flow (Pipeline)\n\n```\n1. INPUT: \"\u0431\u044e\u0434\u0436\u0435\u0442 \u0433\u0434\u0435 \u0442\u043e \u0434\u0432\u0435\u0441\u0438 \u043f\u044f\u0442\u044c\u0434\u0435\u0441\u044f\u0442 \u0442\u044b\u0441\u044f\u0447\"\n         \u2502\n2. ASR Preprocessing (_asr_preprocess)\n   - Correct known distortions: \"\u0434\u0432\u0435\u0441\u0438\" \u2192 \"\u0434\u0432\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0438\"\n         \u2502\n3. Tokenization: split by whitespace\n   [\"\u0431\u044e\u0434\u0436\u0435\u0442\", \"\u0433\u0434\u0435\", \"\u0442\u043e\", \"\u0434\u0432\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0438\", \"\u043f\u044f\u0442\u044c\u0434\u0435\u0441\u044f\u0442\", \"\u0442\u044b\u0441\u044f\u0447\"]\n         \u2502\n4. Lookup (lookup_word / classify)\n   - \"\u0434\u0432\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0438\"  \u2192 (200, mag=3, cardinal)\n   - \"\u043f\u044f\u0442\u044c\u0434\u0435\u0441\u044f\u0442\" \u2192 (50, mag=2, cardinal)\n   - \"\u0442\u044b\u0441\u044f\u0447\"   \u2192 (1000, mag=4, multiplier)\n         \u2502\n5. Group collection: contiguous numeral tokens\n   [(200,3), (50,2), (1000,4)]\n         \u2502\n6. Parse (parse_number_group / parse_sequence)\n   - mag decreases (3\u21922): sum \u2192 200 + 50 = 250\n   - multiplier: 250 \u00d7 1000 = 250000\n         \u2502\n7. Replacement: number tokens \u2192 \"250000\"\n         \u2502\n8. OUTPUT: \"\u0431\u044e\u0434\u0436\u0435\u0442 \u0433\u0434\u0435 \u0442\u043e 250000\"\n         \u2502\n   [OPTIONAL] if confidence < 0.75:\n      \u2192 ruT5-small fallback for difficult cases\n```\n\n### Quality Assurance\n- **Tests**: `pytest` with 27 tests covering both the old parser and the new sequence parser\n- **CI/CD**: Docker-based reproducible builds with multi-stage Dockerfile\n- **Experiment tracking**: MLflow logs parameters, metrics, artifacts, and confusion matrices for every training run\n- **Reports**: Timestamped experiment reports in `reports/` tracking accuracy improvements, planned features, and analysis\n- **Notebook validation**: `scripts/validate_notebook.py` enforces notebook quality standards (nbformat v4, required sections, Polars usage, no inline datasets)\n\n### Relation to Original Task\nThe project is a solution to a **test assignment** (described in `task/\u0422\u0435\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u0434\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043d\u0430 DS.md`) for a Data Scientist position at Avito (a Russian classifieds platform). The assignment required building an ITN system for Russian ASR call transcriptions with numerical expressions, using only local models (no external API calls). The solution achieves **97.6% accuracy** on the provided calibration dataset.\n</task_result>\n</task>",
